sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cinI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: cinI codes for an autoinducer synthetase which utilizes SAM to make O3-C14:1-HSL. In complex with O3-C14:1-HSL, CinR (BBa_C0077) binds to the Cin promoter (BBa_R0077) and activates transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: crackdots
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
The regulatory locus cinRI in Rhizobium leguminosarum conrols a network of quorum-sensing loci Lithgow, JK; Wilkinson, A; Hardman, A; Rodelas, B; Wisniewski-Dye, F; Williams, P; Downie, AJ MOL. MICROBIOLOGY 37(1): 81-97, 2000

Change log: original STOP: tga -> tAaTAA

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: RBS based on Elowitz repressilator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K091146
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: K091146 is a modified version of the pLas' promoter (BBa_K091117) containing the addition of a luxR binding site between the -35 and -10 regions. This promoter is expected to be activated in the presence of PAI-1 and LasR and repressed in the presence of AI-1 and LuxR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erin Feeney
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The LuxR binding site is from BBa_R0062 and the pLas' promoter is from the region upstream of the LasI gene in Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The Lux box was placed adjacent to the LasR binding site with the aim of minimizing cross-talk in the presence of both PAI-1 and AI-1; since the LasR site should have a higher affinity, we hope that the binding of PAI-1 will competitively exclude the binding of AI-1.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: tetA(C)b
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding region for Tetracyline resistance in the reverse orientation. If a promoter adn RBS are placed downstream and the entire region, from promoter to stop codon is flipped the cell will express tetracycline resistance.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K091146
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: K091146 is a modified version of the pLas' promoter (BBa_K091117) containing the addition of a luxR binding site between the -35 and -10 regions. This promoter is expected to be activated in the presence of PAI-1 and LasR and repressed in the presence of AI-1 and LuxR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Erin Feeney
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The LuxR binding site is from BBa_R0062 and the pLas' promoter is from the region upstream of the LasI gene in Pseudomonas aeruginosa.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The Lux box was placed adjacent to the LasR binding site with the aim of minimizing cross-talk in the presence of both PAI-1 and AI-1; since the LasR site should have a higher affinity, we hope that the binding of PAI-1 will competitively exclude the binding of AI-1.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
